title: Police identify victims in fatal Albuquerque shooting
content:
ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. (KRQE) – On Monday, police were at the scene of a shooting in northeast Albuquerque. More information is being released about the incident.
Police say four men had been shot in a house on the 300 block of General Marshall.
Two of those men, 23-year-old Juan Carlos Saenz-Ponce and 24 year old Daniel Chumacero, died after the shooting. The two other men are at the hospital in serious condition.
Police say they do not believe the incident was a random attack.
No arrests have been made.
